AFRICA Caribbean Heritage Alliance (ACHA) has called for proposals for the ‘Nothing About Us Without Us’ (NOW Us!) awards. The theme for the project is inclusiveness in recognition of inspiring and inclusive initiatives from Nigeria, which could promote diversity, innovation as well as creativity, and empower rights holders groups, communities through small grant funding. Calls for proposals are initiated by Voice Nigeria, coordinated by Oxfam in Nigeria, and funded by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in Netherlands, with Africa Caribbean Heritage Alliance (ACHA) as partners.   Rivers approves N8.2b for 10th flyover     Lagos ready to combat flooding, says Igbokwe     ‘See your ordination as service to humanity’   The project is for two years and was officially initiated in October. Deadline for proposals is February 4, and a link has been provided to ease the process. ACHA said three projects would be selected to receive grants of 10,000, 15,000 and 25,000 Euros to carry out activities with community stakeholders. - Advertisement - This development funding opportunity, ACHA noted, supports Nigeria’s efforts to achieve the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) with no one being left behind. It also encourages citizen’s participation in the implementation of social, economic, cultural, political and environmental issues.